      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QOIs directly linked to clinical decision criteria and regulatory submission requirements for spinal implant mechanical performance.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness and failure load are the primary mechanical performance endpoints specified in FDA guidance for pedicle screw systems and directly support 510(k) substantial equivalence argument. QOIs mapped to clinical risk scenarios in the device risk management file."
    },
